{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-detail-js","path":"/post/how-to-install-magento-2-on-mac-a-complete-guide-using-apache-nginx-mysql-mariadb-and-php-7-x/","result":{"data":{"wpPost":{"title":"How to Install Magento 2 on Mac","content":"\n<p>Hello there! If you&#8217;re looking to install the latest version of Magento 2 on a MAC OSX system, you&#8217;ve come to the right place. In this guide, I&#8217;m going to walk you through the process step-by-step so that you can get up and running in no time.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Before we get started, let&#8217;s talk about the tools we&#8217;re going to need. We&#8217;ll be using Apache or Nginx as our web server, MySQL or MariaDB as our database, and PHP 7. x from either the Magento repository or Github. If you don&#8217;t already have these installed, don&#8217;t worry &#8211; I&#8217;ll show you how to do that too.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s dive into the installation process. We&#8217;ll start by downloading the latest version of Magento 2 onto our MAC OSX system. Once we have the files, we&#8217;ll need to set up our web server, configure our database, and install PHP. This may sound daunting, but I promise it&#8217;s not as complicated as it seems.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One thing to note is that I&#8217;m going to be demonstrating how to <a href=\"/how-to-install-magento-2-in-windows-xampp/\">install Magento 2</a> on the latest version of Ubuntu with Apache2 and MariaDB. However, if you&#8217;re using a different operating system or web server, don&#8217;t worry &#8211; the process is pretty similar across the board.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In addition to the installation steps, I&#8217;ll also be providing some tips and tricks along the way to help you avoid common pitfalls and optimize your Magento 2 installation.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>So, if you&#8217;re ready to get started, let&#8217;s dive in and learn <strong><em>how to install Magento 2 on MAC</em></strong> OSX system. By the end of this guide, you&#8217;ll have a fully functional Magento 2 installation up and running, ready to power your online store.</p>\n\n\n\n<h1 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>How to Install Magento 2 on Mac: A Comprehensive Guide Using Apache/Nginx, MySQL/MariaDB, and PHP 7.x</strong></h1>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 1: Set up MAMP</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>MAMP is the most popular local web development solution for Mac OSX. It is free and includes Apache or Nginx, PHP or Python, Perl, or Ruby.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>1. To download the latest version <a href=\"https://www.mamp.info/en/windows/\">here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>2. Open and install MAMP Application for your Mac:</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1301 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:618px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;434&#x27;%20width=&#x27;618&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"1\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition:opacity 250ms linear;width:100%;will-change:opacity;opacity:0\" sizes=\"(min-width: 618px) 618px, 100vw\" decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" data-src=\"/_gatsby/image/bca1eae0ab255145f19467116f28d444/965ce06c3173137c51add60dd8c0ee94/How-to-Install-Magento-2-on-Mac-01-1.png?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwebguru.dev%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F03%2FHow-to-Install-Magento-2-on-Mac-01-1.png&amp;a=w%3D155%26h%3D109%26fm%3Dpng%26q%3D90&amp;cd=2023-03-10T10%3A54%