 manually or use the command line to install it.</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><em>curl -sS https://getcomposer.org/installer | sudo php -- --install-dir=/usr/local/bin --filename=composer</em></code></pre>\n\n\n\n<p>To verify if Composer has been successfully installed, type:</p>\n\n\n\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code\"><code><em>composer -v</em></code></pre>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 3: Obtaining the Magento 2 Package</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>You have several options for downloading the Magento 2 package:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento&#8217;s official website at <a href=\"https://magento.com/tech-resources/download\">https://magento.com/tech-resources/download</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>GitHub repository at <a href=\"https://github.com/magento/magento2/releases\">https://github.com/magento/magento2/releases</a></p>\n\n\n\n<p>Once you have downloaded the package, extract it to the /Applications/MAMP/htdocs/ directory, creating a new folder (e.g., &#8220;magento2&#8221;) within the htdocs directory.&nbsp;</p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Step 4: Setting up Magento 2</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>To begin the installation process, navigate to http://localhost/magento2 in your web browser. This will bring up the Magento Setup Wizard as shown below:</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(1) Initiating the Installation</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Click the &#8216;Start Readiness Check&#8217; button. If any errors are displayed, they must be resolved before continuing. You may click &#8216;More detail&#8217; (if available) for additional information about each check.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(2) Creating a Database</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter the required database information and click &#8216;Next&#8217;.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(3) Configuring the Web Settings</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Enter the following information:</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Your Store Address: http://localhost/magento2</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Magento Admin Address: The relative URL you want to use to access the Admin (e.g. &#8220;secret&#8221; or &#8220;backend&#8221;).</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>(4) Customizing Your Store</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>From the &#8216;Store Default Time Zone list, select the time zone that corresponds to your store location.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>From the &#8216;Store Default Currency&#8217; list, choose the currency you want to use as the default in your store.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>From the &#8216;Store Default Language&#8217; list, select the language you want to use as the default in your store.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>You can also expand the &#8216;Advanced Modules Configuration&#8217; section to enable or disable specific modules before installing the Magento software.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>In this step, you have the option to install Sample Data or not.</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed.</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Greetings! If you&#8217;re planning to install Magento 2 on your Mac, there are a few things you should keep in mind to ensure a smooth and hassle-free installation process.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>One important consideration is the &#8220;Skip dependency check for individual modules&#8221; option. While it may be tempting to use this option to speed up the installation process, it&#8217;s important to use it with caution. This option can lead to errors, particularly if you&#8217;ve manually edited the deployment configuration. So, it&#8217;s best to avoid using this option if possible.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s also worth noting that any manual changes made to the deployment configuration may be undone by future Magento software updates. So, unless you have a very good reason to make manual changes to the configuration, it&#8217;s generally not recommended.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>To ensure a successful installation of Magento 2 on your Mac, it&#8217;s best to follow a proper installation guide that walks you through all the recommended steps. This will help ensure that all necessary dependency checks are performed and that your installation is stable and reliable.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>With the right guidance on <strong><em>how to install Magento 2 on Mac</em></strong> can be a relatively painless process. So, don&#8217;t be afraid to dive in and give it a try! Just be sure to follow the recommended steps and avoid taking shortcuts that could lead to problems down the line.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>By taking the time to properly install Magento 2 on your Mac, you&#8217;ll be well on your way to creating a powerful and flexible e-commerce platform that can help take your business to the next level. Good luck!</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(5) Setting up the Admin Account</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Enter the following information to create the admin account:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li>New Username</li>\n\n\n\n<li>New E-Mail</li>\n\n\n\n<li>New Password</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Confirm Password</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Click &#8216;Next&#8217; to proceed.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>(6) Install</p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><div data-gatsby-image-wrapper=\"\" style=\"position:relative;overflow:hidden;display:inline-block;vertical-align:top\" class=\"gatsby-image-wrapper gatsby-image-wrapper-constrained wp-image-1393 inline-gatsby-image-wrapper\"><div style=\"max-width:963px;display:block\"><img alt=\"\" role=\"presentation\" aria-hidden=\"true\" src=\"data:image/svg+xml;charset=utf-8,%3Csvg%20height=&#x27;400&#x27;%20width=&#x27;963&#x27;%20xmlns=&#x27;http://www.w3.org/2000/svg&#x27;%20version=&#x27;1.1&#x27;%3E%3C/svg%3E\" style=\"max-width:100%;display:block;position:static\"/></div><div aria-hidden=\"true\" data-placeholder-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;width:100%\"></div><img data-gatsby-image-ssr=\"\" data-wp-inline-image=\"5\" data-main-image=\"\" style=\"height:100%;left:0;position:absolute;top:0;transform:translateZ(0);transition